result.execSummary:
Nicolas D Ulloa was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Nicolas D Ulloa was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: appointing Luis Gutierrez for the defendant
Review hearing on June 20, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Warrant for Commitment, signed by Judge Schimel on 05/19/2022.

09:27 AM Defendant Nicolas D Ulloa in court, in custody. Attorney Luis Gutierrez appears as friend of the court. Peter Michael Tempelis appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Atty Gutierrez states that Defendant wants to waive extradition hearing.  

Defense also wants to address bail and time limits. 

Court passes case for forms to be brought up from DA's office. 

Defendant signed waiver of extradition. Atty Herbers now appears for the Defendant as friend of the Court. 

Court conducts colloquy with the Defendant regarding waiver of extradition. 
Defendant requests to waive extradition. Paperwork signed.
Court accepts the Defendant's waiver of extradition and signs off on the waiver. 
Court also signs Warrant for commitment. 
State of Texas to be notified ASAP to pick up the Defendant. If Defendant not picked up by next court date, court can address bail or dismissing the case. If Defendant picked up by next court date, hearing can be removed from the Court's calendar.  Review hearing scheduled for June 20, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Extradition hearing on May 19, 2022 at 08:30 am.

02:28 PM Defendant Nicolas D Ulloa in court with attorney Nicole Marie Ostrowski.   Attorney appears as friend of the court.  District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and waives reading of complaint.  
Service admitted/advised of charges and potential penalties.  
Court advises of right of extradition.
Court advises of right to an attorney.
Attorney Ostrowski states that the Defendant want to contest the extradition as the matter may be resolved and will re-evaluate the Defendant prior to the next court date.
The Court will adjourn to the Trial Court.

The State gives its bail recommendation.
The Defense gives its bail recommendation.
THE COURT REMANDS THE DEFENDANT INTO THE CUSTODY OF THE WAUKESHA COUNTY JAIL.  Extradition hearing scheduled for May 19, 2022 at 08:30 am.
